special_clause_free_text__c:
Pet Clause
Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep 1 Dog on the Property provided that 
(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage 
(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
(iv) it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property
special_clause_free_text__c-2:
Change Of Sharer Clause 

1. Katherine McCowage and Amber Dacres shall cease to be Tenants of the above property and shall have no claim on the deposit monies held as detailed in Clause B6 of the above Lease which deposit shall continue to be held by Grainger Residential Management Ltd. 
2. Lucy Hackett and Ella Fleming will become Tenants of the above property and shall assume joint and several responsibility for the rent and all other terms, conditions and obligations detailed within the above Tenancy Agreement.
3. Lucy Hackett and Ella Fleming shall reimburse Katherine McCowage and Amber Dacres the proportion of the deposit monies detailed in B.6 of the above Tenancy Agreement paid by them less any agreed offset for damage which may have occurred during the period from the original commencement of the Tenancy to the commencement of this Tenancy Agreement. 
4. GRML will have no involvement in the settlement of the outgoing tenants deposit or any issues regarding the current condition of the property with the incoming tenant(s). These matters and the exchange of funds will be resolved between the two parties named in points 1 and 2 above.
5. Lucy Hackett and Ella Fleming shall accept the Inventory Check-In Report effected at the commencement of the Tenancy and assume joint and several responsibility for all and any damage (save for fair wear and tear) to the Property or its fixtures and furniture with effect from the commencement of that Tenancy from 15/05/2021.

Tenant Break Clause
The landlord agrees that the tenant has the right to end the tenancy by giving us written notice. In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time after from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice and cannot expire in the months of December or January. 

Landlord Break Clause
You agree that we may end the tenancy by giving you written notice. The law requires us to give you two months’ notice under Section 21 of the Housing Act 1988 if we wish to end the tenancy. In order to end the tenancy early we may serve on you a Section 21 notice at any time from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B5 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in the Section 21 notice, which will be at least two months from the date of service of the notice.

special_clause_free_text__c-2:
Tenant Break Clause
The landlord agrees that the tenant has the right to end the tenancy by giving us written notice. In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time after from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice and cannot expire in the months of December or January. 

Landlord Break Clause
You agree that we may end the tenancy by giving you written notice. The law requires us to give you two months’ notice under Section 21 of the Housing Act 1988 if we wish to end the tenancy. In order to end the tenancy early we may serve on you a Section 21 notice at any time from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B5 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in the Section 21 notice, which will be at least two months from the date of service of the notice.

special_clause_free_text__c:
The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep 2 Dogs on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

Tenant Break Clause
The landlord agrees that the tenant has the right to end the tenancy by giving us written notice. In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time after from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice and cannot expire in the months of December or January. 

Landlord Break Clause
You agree that we may end the tenancy by giving you written notice. The law requires us to give you two months’ notice under Section 21 of the Housing Act 1988 if we wish to end the tenancy. In order to end the tenancy early we may serve on you a Section 21 notice at any time from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B5 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in the Section 21 notice, which will be at least two months from the date of service of the notice.

PET CLAUSE

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

special_clause_free_text__c:
1.	Not use locked cupboards in bedrooms

The locked cupboard marked with a No Entry sign in one of the bedrooms does NOT form part of the Tenancy and the Tenant shall not use the locked cupboard for their own use or for any other reason. The Tenant confirms that they have been provided with an information sheet confirming the reason for this restriction at the time of signing the tenancy agreement. No attempt shall be made to unlock these doors other than for reasons of an emergency as detailed in Clause X.2 under. 

2.	De-activation of sprinkler system alarm panel

In the event of the sprinkler system activating the Tenant shall be permitted to open the locked cupboard housing the sprinkler system in order to input the alarm code with which they have been provided at the commencement of the Tenancy to de-activate the alarm system. No other access to this locked area shall be permitted. For the avoidance of doubt any costs incurred by the Landlord for the remedy of any malicious damage to the system and any resulting water damage which shall be found to be as a result of the Tenants breach of this clause or clause X.1 above shall be charged to the Tenant in line with Clauses E30 and E31 of this agreement. 

3.	Not interfere with the Ventilation Unit and electrical fused spur linked to it

the Tenant confirms that at the time of signing this agreement they have been provided with an information sheet detailing the location of the ventilation unit and fused spur linked to it. The Tenant shall not touch or tamper with this unit or the fused spur linked to it. For the avoidance of doubt and costs incurred by the Landlord for the remedy of any damage caused to the system as a result of the Tenants breach of this clause shall be charged to the Tenant in line with Clauses E30 and E31 of this agreement.

Pet Clause
Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the 
Tenant may keep 1 Dog on the Property provided that 
(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents 
or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other 
item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage 
(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and 
treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident 
during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy
(iv) it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of 
the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the 
Property

Rent in Advance 
Further to Section B, Clauses 5 and 6 of this Agreement it is further agreed that Fatima 
Alshaikhmubarak shall pay their rent amount for the first 3 months of this Agreement in 
one sum of ¬£4620.00 payable in advance on the signing of this agreement. The tenant(s) 
must then make a further 3 months‚Äô advance payment of ¬£4620.00 no later than the 
01/06/2023, 01/09/2023 and 01/12/2023 for the remainder of the tenancy period. At the end of this tenancy should the 
tenant(s) seek a New Agreement and should the Landlord agree to this, the tenant(s) agree 
to pay for further referencing to determine whether they can pay monthly in advance for 
the new term or whether as a result of the referencing the Landlord shall require payment 
in advance for the whole term. In either case the tenant(s) undertakes to comply with the 
Landlord or his agents‚Äô instructions with regard to payment and to make such payment 
promptly and in line with the provisions of this Agreement.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination.

special_clause_free_text__c:
Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination.

In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. Pet Clause
Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the 
Tenant may keep 1 Dog on the Property provided that 
(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents 
or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other 
item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage 
(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and 
treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident 
during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy
(iv) it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of 
the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the 
Property

special_clause_free_text__c:
Payment of Initial Monies:

The tenants agree to pay as part of their initial statement of monies the full rent for June 2023 in addition to the rent for the period 13/05/2023 ‚Äì 31/05/2023 and the security deposit. This has been agreed due to the tenants‚Äô period of unemployment from 13/05/2023 ‚Äì 03/07/2023. This special clause will supersede the payment schedule detailed in Attachment 5 at the end of this agreement.

RTR Occupation Clause

Not to allow any adult to occupy the Premises unless such person has complied with the requirements of the Immigration Act 2014 (Right to Rent), by providing at his own expense evidence of such to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent. Further not to allow any adult to remain in the Premises once his Right to Rent has expired unless such person can provide at his own expense further evidence of his continued Right to Rent to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent.

special_clause_free_text__c:
PET CLAUSE

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a dog on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

Tenant Break Clause (Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the work relocation necessitates the termination.

Tenant may keep 1 Dog on the Property provided that

or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other

during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the 
Property

special_clause_free_text__c:
Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase or Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase or work relocation necessitates the termination

special_clause_free_text__c:
PET CLAUSE

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

special_clause_free_text__c:
Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination.

RTR Occupation Clause

Not to allow any adult to occupy the Premises unless such person has complied with the requirements of the Immigration Act 2014 (Right to Rent), by providing at his own expense evidence of such to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent. Further not to allow any adult to remain in the Premises once his Right to Rent has expired unless such person can provide at his own expense further evidence of his continued Right to Rent to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent.

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

The tenant(s) must them make a further 6 months‚Äô advance payment of ¬£20,160.00 no later than the August 2022 for the remainder of the tenancy period. At the end of this tenancy should the tenant(s) seek a New Agreement and should the Landlord agree to this, the tenant(s) agree to pay for further referencing to determine whether they can pay monthly in advance for the new term or whether as a result of the referencing the Landlord shall require payment in advance for the whole term. In either case the tenant(s) undertakes to comply with the Landlord or his agents‚Äô instructions with regard to payment and to make such payment promptly and in line with the provisions of this Agreement.

special_clause_free_text__c:
PET CLAUSE

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep 2 cats on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

special_clause_free_text__c-2:
Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

Change of sharer

b. Reece Gannon shall become a Tenant of the property and shall assume joint and several responsibility for the rent and all other terms, conditions and obligations detailed within this Tenancy Agreement.
c. Reece Gannon shall reimburse Daniel Girling-Jones a proportion of the deposit monies detailed in Clause 2.7 or B.6 of this Tenancy Agreement paid by them less any agreed offset for damage which may have occurred during the period from the commencement of the Tenancy the commencement of this Assignment. 
d. Reece Gannon shall accept the Inventory Check-In Report effected at the commencement of the Tenancy and assume joint and several responsibility for all and any damage (save for fair wear and tear) to the Property or its fixtures and furniture with effect from the commencement of that Tenancy created.
e. GRML will not be involved in the settlement of the outgoing tenants deposit or any issues regarding the current condition of the property with the incoming tenant. These matters and the exchange of funds will be resolved between the two parties named in points 1A and 1B above.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination.

PET CLAUSE

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep 2 cats on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination

Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep 2 Cats on the Property provided that

(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property

(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage

(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

special_clause_free_text__c:
Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination

1. Haoran Cao shall cease to be a Tenant of the above property and shall have no claim on the deposit monies held as detailed in Clause B6 of the above Lease which deposit shall continue to be held by Grainger Residential Management Ltd. 
2.  Kexin Li shall become a Tenant of the above property and shall assume joint and several responsibility for the rent and all other terms, conditions and obligations detailed within the above Tenancy Agreement.
3.  Kexin Li shall reimburse Haoran Cao the proportion of the deposit monies detailed in B.6 of the above Tenancy Agreement paid by them less any agreed offset for damage which may have occurred during the period from the original commencement of the Tenancy to the commencement of this Tenancy Agreement. 
4. GRML will have no involvement in the settlement of the outgoing tenants deposit or any issues regarding the current condition of the property with the incoming tenant(s). These matters and the exchange of funds will be resolved between the two parties named in points 1 and 2 above.
5.  Kexin Li shall accept the Inventory Check-In Report effected at the commencement of the Tenancy and assume joint and several responsibility for all and any damage (save for fair wear and tear) to the Property or its fixtures and furniture with effect from the commencement of that Tenancy created on 2nd September 2022.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination

special_clause_free_text__c:
St Anne‚Äôs Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

1.	Rent in Advance 
Further to Section B, Clauses 5 and 6 of this Agreement it is further agreed that Abdulrahman Mohamed, Salem Salem & Ebrahim Salem shall pay their rent amount for the second 6 months of this Agreement in one sum of ¬£8220.00 payable in advance as per the previous agreement dated 03/09/2023. This sum shall be paid on or before the 03/01/2024 and not on the first of the month as expressed in Clause B5. At the end of this tenancy should the tenant(s) seek a New Agreement and should the Landlord agree to this, the tenant(s) agree to pay for further referencing to determine whether they can pay monthly in advance for the new term or whether as a result of the referencing the Landlord shall require payment in advance for the whole term. In either case the tenant(s) undertakes to comply with the Landlord or his agents‚Äô instructions with regard to payment and to make such payment promptly and in line with the provisions of this Agreement.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination

RTR Occupation Clause

Not to allow any adult to occupy the Premises unless such person has complied with the requirements of the Immigration Act 2014 (Right to Rent), by providing at his own expense evidence of such to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent. Further not to allow any adult to remain in the Premises once his Right to Rent has expired unless such person can provide at his own expense further evidence of his continued Right to Rent to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent.

The landlord agrees to a rent credit of one months rent, to be applied at the beginning of the tenancy.

special_clause_free_text__c:
Pet Clause

Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a dog on the Property provided that 
(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage 
(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
(iv) it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property
Paying 6 months rent in advance, then second six months rent on the fourth month.

St Anne's Water Re-Charge
For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase or Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase or work relocation necessitates the termination.

St Anne‚Äôs Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

RTR Occupation Clause

Not to allow any adult to occupy the Premises unless such person has complied with the requirements of the Immigration Act 2014 (Right to Rent), by providing at his own expense evidence of such to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent. Further not to allow any adult to remain in the Premises once his Right to Rent has expired unless such person can provide at his own expense further evidence of his continued Right to Rent to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent

special_clause_free_text__c-2:
1. Pet Clause 
Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the
Tenant may keep 1 cat on the Property provided that
(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents
or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other
item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and
treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident
during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy.

special_clause_free_text__c:
St Anne's Water Re-Charge
For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

special_clause_free_text__c-2:
Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase or Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase or work relocation necessitates the termination.

special_clause_free_text__c:
The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a Rabbit on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase necessitates the termination.

Further to Section B, Clauses 5 and 6 of this Agreement it is further agreed that Miss Emelie Ash shall pay their rent amount as detailed in the Initial Statement of Monies for the initial first 6 months of this Agreement in one sum of ¬£4,100.00 payable in advance on the signing of this agreement. The tenant(s) must them make a further 6 months‚Äô advance payment of ¬£4,100.00 no later than the 28th February 2023. The tenant must then make a 3rd payment of ¬£4284.48 no later than 28 August 2023. The tenant then needs to pay a final payment of ¬£4,284.48 no later than 28 February 2024 for the remainder of the tenancy period. At the end of this tenancy should the tenant(s) seek a New Agreement and should the Landlord agree to this, the tenant(s) agree to pay for further referencing to determine whether they can pay monthly in advance for the new term or whether as a result of the referencing the Landlord shall require payment in advance for the whole term. In either case the tenant(s) undertakes to comply with the Landlord or his agents‚Äô instructions with regard to payment and to make such payment promptly and in line with the provisions of this Agreement.

6. Landlord break clause 
You agree that we may end the tenancy by giving you written notice. The law requires us to give you two months‚Äô notice under Section 21 of the Housing Act 1988 if we wish to end the tenancy. In order to end the tenancy early we may serve on you a Section 21 notice at any time after four months from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. Not to allow any adult to occupy the Premises unless such person has complied with the requirements of the Immigration Act 2014 (Right to Rent), by providing at his own expense evidence of such to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent. special_clause_free_text__c:
St Anne‚Äôs Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

special_clause_free_text__c:
Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase or Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase or work relocation necessitates the termination.

1. Shuyu Xiong shall cease to be a Tenant of the above property and shall have no claim on the deposit monies held as detailed in Clause B6 of the above Lease which deposit shall continue to be held by Grainger Residential Management Ltd. 
2. Yuanchun Zhuang shall become a Tenant of the above property and shall assume joint and several responsibility for the rent and all other terms, conditions and obligations detailed within the above Tenancy Agreement.
3. Yuanchun Zhuang shall reimburse Shuyu Xiong the proportion of the deposit monies detailed in B.6 of the above Tenancy Agreement paid by them less any agreed offset for damage which may have occurred during the period from the original commencement of the Tenancy to the commencement of this Tenancy Agreement. 
4. GRML will have no involvement in the settlement of the outgoing tenants deposit or any issues regarding the current condition of the property with the incoming tenant(s). These matters and the exchange of funds will be resolved between the two parties named in points 1 and 2 above.
5. Yuanchun Zhuang shall accept the Inventory Check-In Report effected at the commencement of the Tenancy and assume joint and several responsibility for all and any damage (save for fair wear and tear) to the Property or its fixtures and furniture with effect from the commencement of that Tenancy created on 15th August 2022.

Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep one cat on the Property provided that; 
(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage 
(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
(iv) it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property.

RTR Occupation Clause

Not to allow any adult to occupy the Premises unless such person has complied with the requirements of the Immigration Act 2014 (Right to Rent), by providing at his own expense evidence of such to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent. Further not to allow any adult to remain in the Premises once his Right to Rent has expired unless such person can provide at his own expense further evidence of his continued Right to Rent to the satisfaction of the Landlord or his Agent

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

special_clause_free_text__c-2:
Tenant Break Clause
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time after ten months from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. 5. Daniel Dale and Max Kelly shall accept the Inventory Check-In Report effected at the commencement of the Tenancy and assume joint and several responsibility for all and any damage (save for fair wear and tear) to the Property or its fixtures and furniture with effect from the commencement of that Tenancy created on 24th June 2021.

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time after ten months from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. Tenant Break Clause
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time after ten months from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. For the avoidance of doubt the earliest date you can end your tenancy is twelve calendar months from the start date of the tenancy.

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a dog on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

2. Ella Hughes will become a Tenant of the above property and shall assume joint and several responsibility for the rent and all other terms, conditions and obligations detailed within the above Tenancy Agreement.
3. Ella Hughes shall reimburse Amy Louise Boardman the proportion of the deposit monies detailed in B.6 of the above Tenancy Agreement paid by them less any agreed offset for damage which may have occurred during the period from the original commencement of the Tenancy to the commencement of this Tenancy Agreement. 
4. GRML will have no involvement in the settlement of the outgoing tenants deposit or any issues regarding the current condition of the property with the incoming tenant(s). These matters and the exchange of funds will be resolved between the two parties named in points 1 and 2 above.
5. Ella Hughes shall accept the Inventory Check-In Report effected at the commencement of the Tenancy and assume joint and several responsibility for all and any damage (save for fair wear and tear) to the Property or its fixtures and furniture with effect from the commencement of that Tenancy from 30/09/2021.
